Package jetbrains.exodus

Interface ByteIterable

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<ByteIterable>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArrayByteIterable, ByteBufferByteIterable, ByteIterableBase, CompoundByteIterable, CompressedUnsignedLongArrayByteIterable, FileByteIterable, FixedLengthByteIterable
    public interface ByteIterable
extends java.lang.Comparable<ByteIterable>
    If working with Environment, any key and value should be a ByteIterable. ByteIterable is a mix of iterable and array. It allows to lazily enumerate bytes without boxing. On the other hand, you can get its length using method getLength(). Generally, iterating over bytes of ByteIterable is performed by means of getting ByteIterator.
    See Also:
    ArrayByteIterable, ByteBufferByteIterable, FileByteIterable, FixedLengthByteIterable, CompoundByteIterable
